BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 194.64 740 Td (THE REASSURANCE-SEEKING CYCLE) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 50 730 m 562 730 l S Q
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 50 705 Td (This is the trap that keeps health anxiety alive:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 680 Td (1. TRIGGER: Notice a body sensation or hear about an illness) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 660 Td (2. THOUGHT: 'What if this is something serious?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 640 Td (3. ANXIETY: Fear/panic rises, body produces MORE symptoms) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 620 Td (4. BEHAVIOR: Google, check body, call doctor, ask partner) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 600 Td (5. BRIEF RELIEF: 'Okay maybe I'm fine...') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 580 Td (6. DOUBT RETURNS: 'But what if they missed something?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 560 Td (7. REPEAT: The cycle starts over, often worse) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 50 530 Td (WHY REASSURANCE DOESN'T WORK:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 510 Td (- Each reassurance teaches your brain it NEEDED reassurance) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 494 Td (- Tolerance builds - you need more reassurance each time) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 478 Td (- It prevents you from learning you can tolerate uncertainty) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 60 462 Td (- It keeps the anxiety alive instead of letting it naturally pass) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 50 431 Td (My most common reassurance-seeking behavior:) Tj ET
q 0.7 G 0.5 w 50 413 m 540 413 l S Q

endstream
